description.narrative: Regional multi-agencies partners are well coordinated and harmonized in support to COs, and tools and evidence are generated and used for advocacy and programming in health, which contributes to Child Health, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses (Covid), Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Operations Support To Programme Delivery. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: ESAR Country Offices achieve Programming Excellence (programmes are gender and equity focused, respond to humanitarian and development contexts, deliver and demonstrate results) by 2021

description.narrative: ESARO actively engaged, managed, and coordinated regional partnerships (H6+, PACT, Africa CDC, IGAD and SADC, Harmonization for Health in Africa and Immunization Regional Working Group) for primary health care (PHC), health emergency preparedness, essential service continuity, and COVID-19 response, that contributed to strengthened coordination system strengthening in the country offices. ;Supporting COVAX;partnership for equitable COVID-19 vaccine access was a top priority. This included vaccine deployment assistance, including country readiness assessments and national vaccine deployment strategy development.ESARO generated evidence to inform action and advocacy around quality of care and domestic health financing, establishing an essential service continuity monitoring system. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/03/2022
